Name: chrisvest$stormpot
RefactoringDetail: Extract And Move Method	package shutdown() : void extracted from public shutdown() : Completion in class stormpot.bpool.BlazePool & moved to class stormpot.bpool.BAllocThread
Message:
shutdown must complete even if allocator eats interrupt signal

if the interrupt happen inside the allocator.allocate(slot) method, and
then the allocator either clears the interruption status, or throws an
interruptedexception which in turn will be understood as poison, then the
allocation thread can miss the shutdown signal, and never begin the
shutdown sequence.

Name: chrisvest$stormpot
RefactoringDetail: Extract And Move Method	package shutdown() : void extracted from public shutdown() : Completion in class stormpot.qpool.QueuePool & moved to class stormpot.qpool.QAllocThread
Message:
shutdown must complete even if allocator eats interrupt signal

if the interrupt happen inside the allocator.allocate(slot) method, and
then the allocator either clears the interruption status, or throws an
interruptedexception which in turn will be understood as poison, then the
allocation thread can miss the shutdown signal, and never begin the
shutdown sequence.

Name: chrisvest$stormpot
RefactoringDetail: Extract Variable	pool : LifecycledPool<GenericPoolable> in method public mustCompleteShutdownEvenIfAllocatorEatsTheInterruptSignal(fixture PoolFixture) : void from class stormpot.PoolTest
Message:
make shutdown more responsive when allocator eats interrupt

when the allocator eats the interrupt, it might turn it into an interruptexception
and poison a slot. the allocator thread would then try to eagerly reallocate that
poisoned slot, thus delaying the shutdown pointlessly.

these changes fixes this. the allocation thread will now skip eager reallocation
if it has been shut down.
